@page
@model MonopHelper.Pages.Version

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Version History";
}

<div class="card">
    <div class="card-header bg-primary text-white">
        @ViewData["Title"]
    </div>
    <div class="card-body bg-light">
        <div class="divider mb-3">
            <h3>1.3 Builds</h3>
            <div class="h-line"></div>

            <h4>Version: 1.3.7</h4>
            <div class="list mb">
                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Added new card actions.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        All cards have the choice to be kept and played based on a condition.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Possible play conditions are none (play anytime), paying rent, paying tax, visiting GO, visiting Jail, visiting Free Parking, rolling a double, or rolling a triple.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        There are 7 possible action types, these are: move, pay, property, dice, reset, take card, and event.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Move actions can be setup for moving a player a number of spaces or advancing to a specific space. It can be setup for forwards or backwards, and for the current player or all players.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Pay actions involve paying or receiving money. This can involve the bank, free parking, or a player. If choosing a player, it can be a specific player, left, right, or all players. Payments/Receive can be based on a multiplier such as houses or hotels.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Property actions allow properties to be taken or handed back to the bank, free parking, or a player. It can either involve a full set or a single property, and can be a swap (two-way).
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Dice actions allow a player's roll to be converted to a double or a triple.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Reset actions can reset a player's jail cost, triple bonus, or properties handed into free parking. It can also be setup for purging a number of properties or sets.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Take card actions will force the player to take a card from each defined card type.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Event actions cause an event to occur: extra turns, miss turns, mortgage properties, jail space, tax spaces, stations, utilities, free parking space, and the GO space.
                        Every event has an end condition: number of turns, rolling a double, rolling a triple, going to jail. There is also a default end condition which occurs when the selected player lands on the space defined in the event.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Actions are split into groups (choices). Each group can have multiple actions of any defined above.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h4>Version: 1.3.6</h4>
            <div class="list mb">
                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Fixed authorisation on turn based game pages.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Fixed custom loan repayment amount and loan repayments on front-end.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Made dropdown panels in turn based games 90% view height.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Added all player's numbers to main screen regardless of who's turn it is.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Can switch to view other players mid-game to perform actions on that player, keeping the current player's turn saved.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Can declare draws in games. This will delete the game and not increase any player's win counts.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Removed card actions. A new implementation of these will be added in the future.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <h4>Version: 1.3.5</h4>
            <div class="list mb">
                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Brand new turn based game
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        In turn based games, you can see who's turn it is and information relating to that player.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        All functionality of the standard game (legacy game) can be done in a turn based game.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Turn based games now track mortgaged properties and calculate the fee a player must pay when passing GO.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Turn based games now track reserved properties and calculate the option fee to pay in order to unlock the reserved properties.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Cards are now in a turn based game.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        Players can be created and selected for games.
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item">
                        The number of wins a player has is tracked.
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        
